Finally, one last quality measurement control we implemented into our group is daily reports. The idea is to regularly report our activities to each other so that everyone is updated on the current progress of the project as a whole.  For our group, we decided to use Facebook to accomplish this mean since it is virtually used by everyone and is most familiar. Our daily reports consist of everyone usually trying to post a status update on their current activity every day and if not, every other day.  We would also ask each other and post problems we bumped into via this method.  This ensured that we were all on the same page regarding the project and as a result should allow us to produce a high quality product.
